# Windows Security Auditng and GPO

This lab shows the audit policy to be configured via Group Policy to ensure relevant security are generated forwarded to Wazuh.

# Home Lab 1 Configure GPO to ensure relevant security

1. First head to Default Domain Controllers Policy and right click edit
- Computer configuration
- policies
- Windows Settings
- Security Settings
- Advanced Audit Policy Configuration

# Enable Audit Categories
1. Head towards Logon/Authentication
- Account Logon → Audit Kerberos Authentication Service
- Account Logon → Audit Kerberos Service Ticket Operations
- Logon/Logoff → Audit Logon
- Logon/Logoff → Audit Account Lockout
Account Management

- Account Management → Audit User Account Management
- Account Management → Audit Security Group Management

Policy Changes

- Policy Change → Audit Audit Policy Change

Directory Services Access
- Policy Change → Audit Directory Service Changes

These settings ensure visibility into authentication attempts, account lifecycle events, privilege changes, and AD object modifications.
